Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @Broccoli{8%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Peel and mince or grate @Ginger{1%thumb}. Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Zest and quarter @Lime{1}.

Toss broccoli on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @Cooking Oil{}, @Salt{}, and @Pepper{}.

Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Cover to keep warm.

Meanwhile, melt @Butter{1%tablespoon} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add half the ginger; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @Jasmine Rice{3/4%cup}, 1 1/4 cups water (2 1/4 cups for 4 servings), and a pinch of salt. Bring to a boil; cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine scallion whites, @White Wine Vinegar{5%teaspoon}, and a pinch of salt. Set aside to pickle.

In a separate small bowl, combine @Sweet Soy Glaze{4%tablespoon}, @Dijon Mustard{2%teaspoon}, remaining ginger, and a squeeze of lime juice.

Pat @Salmon{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Add salmon, skin sides down; cook until skin is lightly browned and crispy, ~{5-7%minutes}. Carefully flip and cook until fish is opaque and cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Add sauce to pan; turn salmon to thoroughly coat. Remove pan from heat.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon}(2 TBSP for 4 servings) and season with salt and pepper.

Toss broccoli with lime zest to taste.

Divide rice, broccoli, and salmon between plates; drizzle salmon with any remaining sauce. Top with pickled scallion whites, scallion greens, and @Sesame Seeds{1%tablespoon}. Drizzle with as much @Sriracha{1%teaspoon} as you like. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Fish is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.